VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT \b(?:ifstream|ofstream|fstream)\b.*\.open\s*\(.*\)
WHEN EXPR MISSING:validate|sanitize|canonical|realpath|filesystem::path
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects file handling operations (`ifstream`, `ofstream`, `fstream`) to ensure they are secure and protected against path traversal vulnerabilities.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Unsafe File Handling: Insecure File Path Usage.
